<section id="how" class="bb-section-band approach-section">
  <div class="bb-container approach-grid">
    <div>
      <div class="bb-eyebrow">Our approach</div>
      <h2 class="bb-display-l">We cannot read<br />your files.</h2>
      <p>
        Files are encrypted on your device with a master key only you hold. Your password
        unlocks that master key locally - we receive the password to authenticate you,
        but never your master key and never your 12-word recovery phrase.
      </p>
      <p class="point">Lose both, lose the data. No backdoor, no exceptions.</p>
      <div class="approach-chips">
        <div><strong>AES-256-GCM</strong><span>industry-standard encryption</span></div>
        <div><strong>12 words</strong><span>your recovery key</span></div>
        <div><strong>Open source</strong><span>audit it yourself</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="approach-cards" aria-label="Encryption approach">
      <div class="approach-card">
        <span>01</span>
        <h3>Key stays local</h3>
        <p>Your master key is created and unlocked on your device.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="approach-card">
        <span>02</span>
        <h3>Files encrypt before upload</h3>
        <p>Names, metadata, and file bytes become ciphertext first.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="approach-card dark">
        <span>03</span>
        <h3>Servers store opaque blobs</h3>
        <p>What reaches Beebeeb is unreadable without keys we never receive.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

